<page>
   <topic>FILE.DRIVE_SPACE_AVAIL Function</topic>
     <description>Returns the number of bytes free on the disk.</description>
   
   <syntax>Byte_Count as N = Drive_Space_Avail(C Drive)</syntax>
   <arguments>
     <argument>
         <name>Drive</name>
         <description>The letter of the drive.</description>
     </argument>
   </arguments>
 
   <discussion>
The FILE.DRIVE_SPACE_AVAIL() method returns the number of bytes of available space on Drive.
   </discussion>
  
   <sections>
       <section><title>Example</title>
            <description>Type the following in the Interactive window:</description>
            <example><![CDATA[
file.drive_space_avail("c:") -> 497418240.000000
]]></example>
       </section>
   </sections>
